{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"773a1910-15d3-428a-bf3a-d366fbc521a4","content":"Here's what I found in `my_app/views.py`:\n\n**`datetime.now()` on line 3** — This is a hardcoded static call that's difficult to mock in tests because it's called directly inside the function body.\n\n### Why it's untestable\nYou can't easily control the return value of `datetime.now()` without patching, which makes time-dependent logic brittle to test.\n\n### Recommended fix\nUse Django's timezone-aware `django.utils.timezone.now` and inject it or use `freezegun`/`unittest.mock.patch`:\n\n```python\nfrom django.utils import timezone\n\ndef index(request):\n    now = timezone.now()\n    return render(request, 'index.html', {'time': now})\n```\n\nThis also fixes a **timezone-awareness issue** — `datetime.now()` returns a naive datetime, while Django expects timezone-aware datetimes when `USE_TZ = True`.\n\nThat's the only file in the project. Just the one instance found.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"754bef83-1636-4547-a8e1-58382410b4bf","outputTokens":236,"requestId":"703B:33B14:44E86D:500582:69F2C0FE"},"id":"8cfdac70-400c-41b6-939e-7a9d47971c72","timestamp":"2026-04-30T02:40:05.366Z","parentId":"1647f118-53cd-4c8a-a813-547c6cf55aad"}
